# Cloudflare Pages static-header rules.
#
# FFmpeg.wasm (used by the in-browser Create Video modal) needs
# SharedArrayBuffer, which the browser only exposes when the page is
# "cross-origin isolated". That requires both COOP and COEP set.
#
# We use COEP: credentialless instead of require-corp so cross-origin
# resources (Firebase Auth iframe, picsum fallback, api.zimbabeats.com
# audio/cover responses, etc.) still load — they're just fetched without
# credentials. The Cloudflare Tunnel responses we own all set CORS
# explicitly so the only places this could surface as a regression are
# embeds from origins we don't control, which the app doesn't load.
/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless
